1
00:00:01,800 --> 00:00:03,510
Instructor: Now I hope you are comfortable

2
00:00:03,510 --> 00:00:05,580
with controllers, actions.

3
00:00:05,580 --> 00:00:09,960
And we are going to add one more hierarchy on top of that.

4
00:00:09,960 --> 00:00:12,090
And the only reason I am showing that

5
00:00:12,090 --> 00:00:14,580
is it is actually a great feature

6
00:00:14,580 --> 00:00:18,180
if you have to divide few things in your project.

7
00:00:18,180 --> 00:00:20,103
And that is called as area.

8
00:00:20,940 --> 00:00:24,660
Typically when we work with routing, we have controller

9
00:00:24,660 --> 00:00:26,820
and then action method.

10
00:00:26,820 --> 00:00:30,450
But .NET team has also provided something special

11
00:00:30,450 --> 00:00:33,900
to divide few things in different areas.

12
00:00:33,900 --> 00:00:37,534
Like if you have a customer facing website and admin panel,

13
00:00:37,534 --> 00:00:41,523
you can divide your project in those two areas.

14
00:00:42,630 --> 00:00:45,810
Now how do you add that in a project?

15
00:00:45,810 --> 00:00:49,320
We will right click on BulkyBookWeb here, add,

16
00:00:49,320 --> 00:00:52,323
and we will click new scaffolded item.

17
00:00:53,790 --> 00:00:57,870
Inside there you can see we have an MVC area.

18
00:00:57,870 --> 00:00:59,400
Let's add that.

19
00:00:59,400 --> 00:01:02,490
And we need to give area a name.

20
00:01:02,490 --> 00:01:05,519
Let's say we have two section in our website.

21
00:01:05,519 --> 00:01:07,980
One is for the admin section,

22
00:01:07,980 --> 00:01:10,830
so let me add an area for admin.

23
00:01:10,830 --> 00:01:14,700
It'll add the NuGet package and scaffold that area.

24
00:01:15,563 --> 00:01:19,950
Another area that we will add will be the customer area

25
00:01:19,950 --> 00:01:23,190
that will have the code related to customer

26
00:01:23,190 --> 00:01:27,004
like homepage, details and much more.

27
00:01:27,004 --> 00:01:28,440
Perfect.

28
00:01:28,440 --> 00:01:30,930
Right here when we scaffold that,

29
00:01:30,930 --> 00:01:34,342
you can see it adds a folder with the name of areas.

30
00:01:34,342 --> 00:01:38,760
Then it has admin, which is the area that we added.

31
00:01:38,760 --> 00:01:42,423
And inside there we have controllers, models and view.

32
00:01:43,590 --> 00:01:46,470
So basically all the code that was previously

33
00:01:46,470 --> 00:01:50,190
just in one location, we can now break that down

34
00:01:50,190 --> 00:01:52,470
in different areas.

35
00:01:52,470 --> 00:01:55,740
But when we add area, you can see the routing here

36
00:01:55,740 --> 00:01:57,780
also changes.

37
00:01:57,780 --> 00:02:01,650
In the scaffold.txt, it displays that, hey,

38
00:02:01,650 --> 00:02:05,163
now you have to add areas in the routing as well.

39
00:02:06,030 --> 00:02:07,710
So let me do that.

40
00:02:07,710 --> 00:02:09,720
Let me copy this.

41
00:02:09,720 --> 00:02:13,230
And we will go to our program.cs.

42
00:02:13,230 --> 00:02:15,630
We have the controller route here.

43
00:02:15,630 --> 00:02:20,193
Let me paste that here and we will add a forward slash.

44
00:02:21,600 --> 00:02:24,840
So now we need to say what area should be invoked

45
00:02:24,840 --> 00:02:28,980
by default, I will call that as customer.

46
00:02:28,980 --> 00:02:33,183
We do not have that, so let me add that area as well.

47
00:02:36,150 --> 00:02:41,150
And we will call that customer area, and let me add that.

48
00:02:43,614 --> 00:02:46,140
Perfect, that looks good.

49
00:02:46,140 --> 00:02:48,920
Now with that, we will have to move our controllers

50
00:02:48,920 --> 00:02:51,750
inside the area folders.

51
00:02:51,750 --> 00:02:54,300
Now in the area you can see we have folder

52
00:02:54,300 --> 00:02:56,280
for data and models,

53
00:02:56,280 --> 00:02:59,190
but we have moved that to the individual project

54
00:02:59,190 --> 00:03:01,830
so we do not need these two here.

55
00:03:01,830 --> 00:03:06,210
Let me delete that from both the areas.

56
00:03:06,210 --> 00:03:07,950
We will only have controllers

57
00:03:07,950 --> 00:03:10,893
and views inside the area Folder.

58
00:03:11,880 --> 00:03:16,320
Category controller belongs to the admin functionality

59
00:03:16,320 --> 00:03:19,803
so I will move that to the admin controller.

60
00:03:20,730 --> 00:03:25,380
Home controller is a customer facing, so I will change that

61
00:03:25,380 --> 00:03:29,070
and move that inside the customer area.

62
00:03:29,070 --> 00:03:32,730
With that, our default route now is customer area,

63
00:03:32,730 --> 00:03:35,553
home controller, and index action.

64
00:03:36,450 --> 00:03:40,620
Now when I moved this, the namespace were also updated,

65
00:03:40,620 --> 00:03:43,290
but if in your case you selected no

66
00:03:43,290 --> 00:03:45,690
and you did not update the namespace,

67
00:03:45,690 --> 00:03:48,147
make sure to update that namespace.

68
00:03:49,440 --> 00:03:52,050
On top of that, how do you tell a controller

69
00:03:52,050 --> 00:03:56,250
that this controller belongs to a specific area?

70
00:03:56,250 --> 00:03:59,370
For that we have the area attribute here.

71
00:03:59,370 --> 00:04:01,770
And we need to give the name

72
00:04:01,770 --> 00:04:06,000
that category controller is inside the admin area

73
00:04:06,000 --> 00:04:10,473
and home controller is inside customer area.

74
00:04:12,530 --> 00:04:16,382
With that configured, let me run the project.

75
00:04:17,910 --> 00:04:19,829
And things are not working.

76
00:04:19,829 --> 00:04:24,120
The constraint customer inside the route option.

77
00:04:24,120 --> 00:04:27,000
Let me see what the route option is.

78
00:04:27,000 --> 00:04:31,623
And of course this will be equal to and not a colon.

79
00:04:33,690 --> 00:04:36,810
Now we have a more user friendly exception,

80
00:04:36,810 --> 00:04:39,690
which says the view was not found.

81
00:04:39,690 --> 00:04:41,760
And that is indeed correct,

82
00:04:41,760 --> 00:04:44,190
because we have moved the controller

83
00:04:44,190 --> 00:04:46,983
but we did not move the corresponding views.

84
00:04:48,000 --> 00:04:50,310
So let me go to the views here,

85
00:04:50,310 --> 00:04:54,840
category, we will move that inside the admin here,

86
00:04:54,840 --> 00:04:59,840
and home, move that to the customer views right here.

87
00:05:01,860 --> 00:05:05,280
Once you move that and if you run the project,

88
00:05:05,280 --> 00:05:07,443
things will still not work.

89
00:05:08,430 --> 00:05:11,790
Where is the namespace, let me see.

90
00:05:11,790 --> 00:05:14,613
It is inside the category views.

91
00:05:15,660 --> 00:05:19,560
And yep, we have the model of category.

92
00:05:19,560 --> 00:05:24,030
But how will we know where exactly is this category?

93
00:05:24,030 --> 00:05:29,030
If you examined, we had that previously in the view imports.

94
00:05:29,130 --> 00:05:30,843
We had dot models.

95
00:05:32,130 --> 00:05:35,700
So along with that we also have to move the view start

96
00:05:35,700 --> 00:05:37,500
and view import.

97
00:05:37,500 --> 00:05:42,500
Both the files, we will paste it inside the view folder

98
00:05:42,570 --> 00:05:44,970
in both the areas.

99
00:05:44,970 --> 00:05:46,413
Perfect.

100
00:05:47,310 --> 00:05:50,463
With that, let me run the project once again.

101
00:05:52,590 --> 00:05:57,540
And perfect, the website comes up and everything looks good.

102
00:05:57,540 --> 00:06:01,500
But when you click on home and privacy, that is working

103
00:06:01,500 --> 00:06:05,460
because both of them are inside the customer area

104
00:06:05,460 --> 00:06:08,610
but category is inside admin area.

105
00:06:08,610 --> 00:06:11,190
When you click there, it tries to look

106
00:06:11,190 --> 00:06:15,453
for category controller in customer, which does not exist.

107
00:06:16,290 --> 00:06:19,050
So we have to modify that.

108
00:06:19,050 --> 00:06:23,370
So what will happen is where we have the asp-controller

109
00:06:23,370 --> 00:06:27,513
now we will also have to define asp-area.

110
00:06:28,620 --> 00:06:31,410
So category is inside admin

111
00:06:31,410 --> 00:06:34,923
and home controller is inside customer.

112
00:06:39,540 --> 00:06:43,530
If you do not write the area, it'll look for that controller

113
00:06:43,530 --> 00:06:47,853
in the existing area where the page is already residing.

114
00:06:48,900 --> 00:06:50,220
That looks good.

115
00:06:50,220 --> 00:06:53,823
Let me run the project and see if that works.

116
00:06:55,042 --> 00:06:55,950
Perfect.

117
00:06:55,950 --> 00:06:58,890
Admin, category, that works.

118
00:06:58,890 --> 00:07:01,980
If you click create new category, it will work

119
00:07:01,980 --> 00:07:05,070
because even if you have not defined the area

120
00:07:05,070 --> 00:07:10,070
we are looking inside the same admin area that we are in.

121
00:07:10,110 --> 00:07:13,740
So you can see create, back to list, edit,

122
00:07:13,740 --> 00:07:15,660
everything is working

123
00:07:15,660 --> 00:07:18,843
because we are working in the same area.

124
00:07:19,680 --> 00:07:21,780
Now typically moving forward,

125
00:07:21,780 --> 00:07:26,190
I will explicitly write all the areas, but for category

126
00:07:26,190 --> 00:07:28,410
I think we are good to skip that

127
00:07:28,410 --> 00:07:31,830
because we will always perform CRUD operations

128
00:07:31,830 --> 00:07:34,053
from the category index page.

129
00:07:35,370 --> 00:07:36,540
But perfect.

130
00:07:36,540 --> 00:07:40,050
With that you can see how areas will add one more layer

131
00:07:40,050 --> 00:07:41,490
in navigation.

132
00:07:41,490 --> 00:07:44,100
And now when we are working with routing

133
00:07:44,100 --> 00:07:47,580
we will define area first, then controller,

134
00:07:47,580 --> 00:07:49,203
and then the action name.

